]] and [[Husk (comics)|Husk]].{{issue|date=December 2012}}\\n\\nEven though Spoilsport seemed rather flighty and superficial, she was an avid warrior. She attacked and bested Paladin, but was later defeated by Jubilee and Skin.{{issue|date=December 2012}}\\n\\nWhen the [[mentally ill]] [[Scarlet Witch]] depowered over 90% of the world\'s mutant population on [[Decimation (comics)|M-Day]], Spoilsport was among the many who lost her powers.<ref>confirmed in \'\'New Avengers #18\'\'</ref>\\n\\n==Powers and abilities==\\nSpoilsport is a mutant with the ability to defy gravity when skating on her inline skates. She can zoom at high speeds up walls and on ceilings without any problem, and frequently uses surprise and her agility to take her opponents down quickly.\\n\\n==Bibliography==\\n*\'\'Generation X\'\' #53-54\\n*\'\'New Avengers\'\' #18 (shown on screen)\\n\\n==References==\\n{{reflist}}\\n\\n==External links==\\n*[http://www.uncannyxmen.net/db/characters/showquestion.asp?fldAuto=1002 Uncannyxmen.net character bio on Spoilsport]\\n\\n[[Category:Fictional criminals]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutants]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\\n\\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}'